pr_title: GSoC Part 1 & 2: Binary Buffer functions, Serialization and Deserialization
pr_body:
This pull request marks the completion of my GSoC Project for Summer 2022, and contains all the commits pertaining to my changes in both the pull requests for Part 1 and Part 2 of my project, which are:
- [GSoC Part 1: Binary Buffer functions](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2309)
- [GSoC Part 2: Serialization and Deserialization](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2317)

Aside from these, I also made the following pull requests which got merged:
- [EDL Parser Implementation: Part 2](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2310)
- [WIP: EDL parser implementation](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2306)
- [WIP: Fixes for macros in EDL lexer](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2305)
- [Bug fixes for DnD implementation in `libEGM`](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2304)
- [Fix more build errors with JDI update](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2295)

Also, I made the following pull requests which did not get merged:
- [feat: add ability for Lexer to add macros to ParseContext](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2312)
- [emake: add -j flags to specify compile jobs](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2307)
- [Fix the 'ouble' bug](https://github.com/enigma-dev/enigma-dev/pull/2300)
- [WIP: Fix `MSVC x86_64` CI](https://github.com/enigma-dev/RadialGM/pull/230)

I tracked my progress approximately weekly on my personal blog: https://dc03.github.io/
